Commentary Text: Mohit Sharma to Zampa, out Zampa Run Out!! 1 run completed. Gee, we have seen everything tonight. Just when you thought it couldn't get any worse for RR, it just did. RR post their lowest total in Jaipur. Zampa lofted this off the toe end and teased the fielder (Shankar) running back from cover. Abhinav came sprinting in from sweeper to his right and collected the ball cleanly before sending a rifle-like throw at the batting end. The call was always for two and Zampa was casually trundling to the batting end probably assuming the only he was could get out was a direct hit. And bam! The ball bounced off the outfield and kept low before striking the stumps dead. Zampa run out (Abhinav Manohar) 7(9)

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Riyan Parag, out Lbw!! This was coming. Rashid not the easiest to read off the hand even if you are a modern day great. So he will fancy his chances v Riyan, which is why he wouldn't have been too unhappy about bowling a short ball for two than a single the previous ball. Googly from Rashid Khan, pitching just outside off stump, Riyan couldn't read it, played across the line, just sneaked past the inside edge to hit him in line with off stump. Ball-tracker shows ball smashing middle of middle stump, so the review too is gone for RR. The impact sub doesn't work. Unfortunately, Riyan was up against a giant. Brilliant captaincy from Hardik to not hold back Rashid for later and go for the kill. Riyan Parag lbw b Rashid Khan 4(6)

Commentary Text: Joshua Little to Samson, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! Oh Sanju! Not again. Surely not after looking so promising. The heartbreak for a cricket fan to see him not convert a start. This was a simple length delivery just around off stump. Sanju moved across the stumps to flick to mid-wicket. Wonder why he did that because the left-armer's angle across RHB is anyway going to make it tougher. This ball did seem to seam away a wee bit. Massive leading edge. Hardik waits ages under the ball at cover and takes a very good catch. Sanju stares at the pitch. Still staring and looking back as he drags himself off unwillingly. Big, big wicket. Sanju was looking so good and the over where Little was losing the battle, he gets the main man. Samson c Hardik Pandya b Joshua Little 30(20) [4s-3 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Samson, out Jaiswal Run Out!! Cut away nicely. Excellent diving save by Abhinav! Oh yes-no, both Sanju and Jaiswal at the keeper's end and Sanju gets back to his crease. Disaster for RR. This was a shortish ball, Sanju timed that nicely, Jaiswal thought he had a run there with this being a half stop and the fielder had to fetch the ball before throwing. Sanju was out of the crease, but saw the fielding and went back. Jaiswal was already at his end by then and the fielder had ample time to relay a calm throw to Rashid's end. Problem for Jaiswal was the half stop went straight to the man at short third man. Jaiswal run out (Mohit Sharma/Rashid Khan) 14(11) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Buttler, out Caught by Mohit Sharma!! Edgeddd and straight to short third man. How perfectly could you place a fielder there?
